Package: rm-trash
Architecture: all
Description: Safely put your removed files into trash for later retrieval.
 rm-trash utility puts the files you delete in a shell safely into the Trash (Recycle bin). 
 The script is meant to be used in place of rm system command in linux .
 rm-trash solves accidental removals and unlike other such utilities and
 it can handle duplicate files in the trash and works for recursive arguments and any other options that rm supports .
